title: For Sale:  Finnish Mosin-Nagant Model M-39
postcontent:
Finnish Mosin-Nagant Model M-39 bolt action 7.62x54R caliber; manufactured by VKT in 1942, the middle of their production which ran from 1940 - 1944, and the early/middle part of the "Continuation War" between Finland and the Soviet Union (1941 - 1944).  The Model M-39 is well known for its accuracy, and at 9½ pounds it absorbs more recoil than the 8¾ pound Russian M-91/30s on the market today.  I have owned this rifle for 9 years.  It has made 1 trip to the range where I fired 20 rounds of Czech Silver-tip before cleaning it thoroughly and storing it.  I have kept it meticulously clean and protected, and its condition reflects this care.  See photos.  It has a beautifully figured ("tiger stripe") pistol grip stock with the normal plug repairs, a square post-war splice, and 3 so-called "kill notches" on the forend.  The front sight is adjustable for windage and the rear sight is adjustable for elevation.  The bore is bright and sharp.  Trigger has smooth take-up and a crisp break.  Comes with the cleaning rod and ammo pouch pictured.

An owners manual for this rifle can be viewed here:  stevespages.com/pdf/century_mosin-nagant-rifles.pdf

FTF transaction.  Must present government picture ID showing you are a resident of Ohio of legal age to purchase this firearm.

High resolution photographs available on request.

postcontent:
Up for sale here is a super nice condition DPMS A2 Dissipator AR-15 rifle.  In case you don't know, a Dissipator upper is a 16" heavy barrel with a 12" rifle length gas system.  This gives you a smooth recoil system with a much longer sight radius but with the same length 16" barrel as a carbine.  This is chamberd in 5.56 and has a 1:9" twist.  This rifle has an A2 buttstock installed, Magpul handguards with 4 Magpul rail sections installed on it.  Command Arms forward stubby grip is included as well.  It also has a DPMS 3 Prong flash hider installed on it.  It handles very nicely and functions 100%.  Although not picture, one 30rd magazine is included with it.  

This is not a cheapy "sporter" type model that have dropped the price on alot of AR15's recently.  I know you can go to Walmart and buy a DPMS Sporter model for $600, this isn't the same model and isn't in the same league quality wise.  It's a full mil-spec gun, all metal parts gun.  It's a very unique rifle that you don't see very often...I just have several AR's at the moment and never get to shoot this one that much.  

I will consider trades of all kinds, mainly interested in handguns.  Cash on your end if the trade doesn't even up, or if you wanna do a 2 for 1 type trade, that works to as long as its a fair trade for each of us.  Asking $1000 OBO

title: For Sale:  Steyr M9A1 w/4 mags, 2 holsters - $550 cash FTF
location: Anywhere in metro area, Des Moines, Iowa
postcontent:
SOLD

I am selling my Steyr M9A1 9mm pistol and accessories and am asking $550 in cash, face-to-face in the DSM area. I have about $720 invested in everything listed. M9A1's have a 4" barrel with conventional rifling and use 15 round flush-fit mags, making them comparable in size to a Glock 19. Pistol was originally purchased with one magazine and I purchased three more at around $30 each which are included.  17 round factory mags (15 round mags with an extended base pad) have been hitting the market recently and will work with this gun.

The pistol is used and has at most 800 rounds down the pipe, but that's on the high end.  There is some minor holster wear on the right side which is shown in detail in the pictures.  Has been boringly reliable for me with brass-cased ammo after replacing the extractor.  It does not like Blazer Aluminum and I have never run any steel-cased 9mm through it, so I couldn't tell you if it will like that or not.  I have taken the time to polish the moving parts in the trigger system and I have replaced the steel striker spring retaining clip with delrin cups by Big Taco.  The pull weight has not been modified, however I have a reduced power striker spring (also by Big Taco) that I can include for free if you wish.  It should not be used for carry as it could cause light strikes. 

There are four mags that come with the pistol, all are 15 round capacity.  Three of the bodies have 14 round witness holes, but will hold 15 rounds.  The fourth magazine is newer production and is marked correctly with a witness hole for the 15th round.  These are all factory mags.

There are two holsters that go with this gun - the first is a right-hand OWB custom kydex holster similar in style to a Raven Concealment holster.  It is made by Keith of Controlled Chaos Arms and was molded specifically to fit this gun - not a blue gun.  It has an FBI cant and 1.5" belt loops. It rides high and tight for good concealment and can be adjusted slightly for increased ride height or +/- cant.  I paid around $60 for this holster.

The second holster is a right-hand Blade-Tech "Level II Tactical" thigh rig.  It has a standard thumb break and adjustable friction retention, as well as a quick detach belt loop. I paid around $120 shipped for this holster.

I will not sell this pistol to you if you do not have a current IA permit to acquire or permit to carry.
